This paper is about a learning method for neuromorphic computing on the TrueNorth chip, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning. Specifically, the paper discusses methods for improving the inference accuracy and optimizing core occupation and performance on the chip. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
